documentation.text: @notice Events for adding and removing various roles
@notice The deployer is automatically given the admin role which will allow them to then grant roles to other addresses

addAdminRole(address).notice: Grants the admin role to an address.
addAdminRole(address).details: The sender must have the admin role.

params._address: EOA or contract receiving the new role.

addMinterRole(address).notice: Grants the minter role to an address
addMinterRole(address).details: The sender must have the admin role

params._address: EOA or contract receiving the new role

addOperatorRole(address).notice: Grants the operator role to an address
addOperatorRole(address).details: The sender must have the admin role

params._address: EOA or contract receiving the new role

addSmartContractRole(address).notice: Grants the smart contract role to an address
addSmartContractRole(address).details: The sender must have the admin role

params._address: EOA or contract receiving the new role

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive. Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point. WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

hasAdminRole(address).notice: Used to check whether an address has the admin role.

returns._0: bool True if the account has the role or false if it does not.

hasMinterRole(address).notice: Used to check whether an address has the minter role

returns._0: bool True if the account has the role or false if it does not

hasOperatorRole(address).notice: Used to check whether an address has the operator role

returns._0: bool True if the account has the role or false if it does not

hasSmartContractRole(address).notice: Used to check whether an address has the smart contract role

returns._0: bool True if the account has the role or false if it does not

removeAdminRole(address).notice: Removes the admin role from an address.
removeAdminRole(address).details: The sender must have the admin role.

removeMinterRole(address).notice: Removes the minter role from an address
removeMinterRole(address).details: The sender must have the admin role

removeOperatorRole(address).notice: Removes the operator role from an address
removeOperatorRole(address).details: The sender must have the admin role

removeSmartContractRole(address).notice: Removes the smart contract role from an address
removeSmartContractRole(address).details: The sender must have the admin role

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

AdminRoleGranted(address,address).notice: Events for adding and removing various roles.

MinterRoleGranted(address,address).notice: Events for adding and removing various roles
